				<h2>What is Customer Lifecycle Automation?</h2>
				<p>Customer lifecycle automation is the strategic use of technology to automatically guide customers through every stage of their relationship with your business—from the moment they discover you to when they become loyal advocates.</p>

				<p>Instead of manually managing each customer interaction, lifecycle automation creates systematic, triggered workflows that deliver the right message, at the right time, through the right channel—all without manual intervention.</p>

				<div class="highlight-box">
					<strong>Why It Matters:</strong> Companies with mature lifecycle automation see 79% higher customer retention rates and 2.5x higher customer lifetime value compared to those relying on manual processes. The reason? Automation ensures no customer falls through the cracks.
				</div>

				<h2>The 8 Customer Lifecycle Stages</h2>
				<p>Understanding the customer journey is the foundation of effective lifecycle automation. Each stage has unique goals, challenges, and automation opportunities.</p>

				<ol>
					<li><strong>Awareness:</strong> Prospect discovers your brand and becomes aware of their problem</li>
					<li><strong>Consideration:</strong> Evaluating your solution against alternatives</li>
					<li><strong>Purchase:</strong> Making the buying decision and becoming a customer</li>
					<li><strong>Onboarding:</strong> Getting started, learning the system, seeing initial value</li>
					<li><strong>Adoption:</strong> Regular use, habit formation, deeper engagement</li>
					<li><strong>Retention:</strong> Staying long-term, renewing, continued satisfaction</li>
					<li><strong>Expansion:</strong> Buying more, upgrading, increasing spend</li>
					<li><strong>Advocacy:</strong> Referring others, leaving reviews, becoming a brand champion</li>
				</ol>

				<h2>How to Automate Each Lifecycle Stage</h2>

				<div class="stage-box">
					<h3>1. Awareness Stage Automation</h3>
					<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Capture attention and generate qualified leads</p>
					<p><strong>Automation Tactics:</strong></p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Lead Capture Automation</strong> - Smart forms that segment leads based on responses</li>
						<li><strong>Lead Magnet Delivery</strong> - Instant delivery of ebooks, guides, templates, calculators</li>
						<li><strong>Content Marketing Automation</strong> - Auto-publish blog posts, social media content</li>
						<li><strong>Retargeting Automation</strong> - Pixel-based campaigns that follow prospects across the web</li>
						<li><strong>Chatbot Qualification</strong> - AI agents that engage website visitors instantly</li>
					</ul>
					<p><strong>Example Workflow:</strong> Visitor downloads guide → Automatically tagged in CRM → Enters nurture sequence → Retargeting ads activate</p>
				</div>

				<div class="stage-box">
					<h3>2. Consideration Stage Automation</h3>
					<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Educate prospects and build trust to move them toward purchase</p>
					<p><strong>Automation Tactics:</strong></p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Nurture Email Sequences</strong> - Multi-touch education campaigns based on interests</li>
						<li><strong>Content Drip Campaigns</strong> - Progressive education that builds on previous content</li>
						<li><strong>Case Study Showcases</strong> - Automatically share relevant success stories based on industry</li>
						<li><strong>Demo Scheduling Automation</strong> - Calendar booking with automatic reminders</li>
						<li><strong>Lead Scoring</strong> - Track engagement to identify hot prospects automatically</li>
						<li><strong>Sales Alert Triggers</strong> - Notify sales team when prospects show buying signals</li>
					</ul>
					<p><strong>CRM Integration:</strong> Track every interaction (email opens, content downloads, website visits) to trigger personalized follow-ups.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="stage-box">
					<h3>3. Purchase Stage Automation</h3>
					<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Remove friction and close the sale</p>
					<p><strong>Automation Tactics:</strong></p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Abandoned Cart Recovery</strong> - Triggered emails when prospects don't complete purchase</li>
						<li><strong>Sales Follow-Up Sequences</strong> - Automatic reminders and value reinforcement</li>
						<li><strong>Proposal Automation</strong> - Generate customized proposals with e-signature capability</li>
						<li><strong>Contract Workflows</strong> - Streamlined signing and onboarding trigger</li>
						<li><strong>Payment Processing</strong> - Automated invoicing and payment reminders</li>
						<li><strong>AI Sales Agents</strong> - Phone calls to answer last-minute questions and close deals</li>
					</ul>
					<p><strong>Example:</strong> Lead goes cold after proposal → Auto-email after 3 days → AI phone agent calls after 7 days → Special limited-time offer after 14 days</p>
				</div>

				<div class="stage-box">
					<h3>4. Onboarding Stage Automation</h3>
					<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Get customers to "aha moment" and first value quickly</p>
